## 🚀 Deployment Instructions

### Step 1: Deploy Backend on Render

1. Push your code to **GitHub** (if not already)
2. Go to [render.com](https://render.com) → **New** → **Web Service**
3. Connect your GitHub repo and **select the `backend` folder** as root directory
4. Configure:

   | Setting | Value |
   |---------|-------|
   | **Name** | `carriermind-api` |
   | **Root Directory** | `backend` |
   | **Runtime** | Node |
   | **Build Command** | `npm install` |
   | **Start Command** | `npm start` |

5. Add **Environment Variables**:

   | Key | Value |
   |-----|-------|
   | `GEMINI_API_KEY` | *your Gemini API key* |
   | `FRONTEND_URL` | *(leave blank for now, add after Vercel deploy)* |

6. Click **Create Web Service** → wait for it to deploy
7. Copy the deployed URL (e.g., `https://carriermind-api.onrender.com`)

---

### Step 2: Deploy Frontend on Vercel

1. Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) → **Add New** → **Project**
2. Import your GitHub repo
3. Configure:

   | Setting | Value |
   |---------|-------|
   | **Root Directory** | `frontend` |
   | **Framework Preset** | Create React App |
   | **Build Command** | `npm run build` |
   | **Output Directory** | `build` |

4. Add **Environment Variable**:

   | Key | Value |
   |-----|-------|
   | `REACT_APP_API_URL` | `https://carriermind-api.onrender.com` *(your Render URL from Step 1)* |

5. Click **Deploy**

---

### Step 3: Update Render CORS

Go back to **Render** dashboard → your service → **Environment**:

| Key | Value |
|-----|-------|
| `FRONTEND_URL` | `https://your-app.vercel.app` *(your Vercel URL from Step 2)* |

Redeploy the backend service after updating.

---

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Never commit your `.env` file with real API keys to Git.** Both `.gitignore` files already exclude `.env`. Always set secrets via the Render/Vercel dashboards.

> [!NOTE]
> Render free tier sleeps after inactivity — the first request after sleep takes ~30-60 seconds. This is normal.
